race.comment: Competitive betting race. SELF SERVE (11) is a progressive mare that hasn't found her ceiling yet. She might be ready to peak after two minor placings this campaign. She's drawn to get all the favours in the run and she gets a valuable 3kg claim for an in-form apprentice. She can win. CAPITALEX (7) was good first-up then fair last time. Forgive the horse one bad run and suspect he can bounce back here. ISLA'S FURY (13) controlled the race and bolted in to break her maiden first-up. This is harder but she's got upside and might be capable of stepping up. She will give herself a chance on speed and can fill a top-three place. Others to think about are STOLEN KISS (8) and TAINO ROCKET (10).
